ADR-06 — Use Django Templates for Server-Side Rendering + Progressive Enhancement
Status: Accepted
Context
The assignment emphasises accessibility and clear architectural reasoning rather than SPA complexity.
Decision
Render the UI using Django templates with lightweight JavaScript enhancements.
Rationale
•	Superior baseline accessibility (WCAG compliance).
•	Simpler tooling and deployment than React.
•	Better alignment with Django’s MVT pattern.
Consequences
Positive: Faster rendering for users, full accessibility, simpler tech stack.
Negative: Less dynamic than SPA frameworks.
